Financial Analysis

Hemant Thapa

Date: 13/11/2022

This is an open-research conducted on Meta (Facebook), All material used during research are free of cost and open-source softwares, such as Jupyter Notebook, Pandas, Numpy, Seaborn, Matplotlib, Python in-built libraries and yahoo finance Api.

Meta has cut down, 13 per cent of its workers, which are nearly 11,000 employees.Meta with the headcount of correction, Meta still accquire more staff than it has last year. In the end of December 2021, the company had almost 72,000 staff, on last Wednesday, the cuts shrank its workforce from more than 85,000 to about 74,000.Nearly $89bn has been wiped from the company’s market capitalisation in late October, when Meta has posted declining revenues. Meta shares closed up more than 5 per cent on Wednesday.

3.2 Quarterly Earning.¶

It shows company is going into loss because revenue is the income of a company generates before deducting expenses. earnings, on the other hand, represents the profit a company has earned.
